<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <header class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold">Documentation</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-400">Step-by-step guide to integrating ExtPay Manager with your extensions.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="space-y-12 prose prose-invert max-w-none">
        <section>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">1. Setup Flutterwave</h3>
            <p>Create a Flutterwave account and get your API keys from the <b>Settings > API Keys</b> section. You'll need the Public Key, Secret Key, and you should define a Secret Hash for webhooks.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">2. Add your Extension</h3>
            <p>Go to the <a href="/extensions" class="text-blue-400">Extensions</a> page and add your extension. The <b>slug</b> is important as it identifies your extension in API calls.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">3. Create Pricing Plans</h3>
            <p>For each extension, create one or more pricing plans. You can choose between One-Time, Monthly, or Yearly payments.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">4. Integrate Checkout</h3>
            <p>Copy the checkout snippet from the <a href="/snippets" class="text-blue-400">Snippets</a> page and add it to your website. This will show a "Buy" button that opens the Flutterwave payment modal.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">5. Verify Licenses in Extension</h3>
            <p>In your Chrome extension's <code>background.js</code> or <code>popup.js</code>, use the verification snippet to check if the user has a valid license key. You should store the license key in <code>chrome.storage.local</code> after the user enters it.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="bg-blue-500/10 border border-blue-500/30 p-6 rounded-2xl">
            <h4 class="text-blue-400 font-bold mb-2">Pro Tip: Webhooks</h4>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">Always configure the webhook URL in Flutterwave. This ensures that even if a user's internet drops after payment, the license will still be generated and the user will receive it via email (if you implement email sending) or can be found in your dashboard.</p>
        </section>
    </div>
</div>
